   "body" : "Following the drop of Python 2 support in the next release (#11881) and specifically [this](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/11881#issuecomment-352668098) comment, I am listing some new Python 3 features that can replace some old ones.\r\n\r\n**New in 3.4**\r\n\r\n- use the pathlib module for [dealing with paths](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/search?l=Python&q=os.path&type=&utf8=%E2%9C%93). see [PEP428](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0428/)\r\n\r\n**New in 3.5**\r\n\r\n- replace [os.listdir](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/search?l=Python&q=os.listdir&type=&utf8=%E2%9C%93) with the much faster os.scandir. see [PEP471](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0471/)\r\n\r\n**New in 3.6**\r\n\r\n- secrets module to replace [os.urandom](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/search?l=Python&q=os.urandom&type=&utf8=%E2%9C%93). see [PEP 506](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0506/)\r\n\r\n- f-strings instead of str.format. see [PEP 498](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0498/)",
